Package com.googlecode.aluminumproject.annotations

Various annotations.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    FunctionClass
    Indicates that the static methods of a class can be used as functions.
    Ignored
    Indicates that a component that would normally have been used should be ignored.
    Injected
    Used to indicate that a field in an action, action contribution, function, or converter is expected to be injected by its factory.
    Named
    Used to override the names that are used for actions, action parameters, action contributions, functions, function arguments, parsers, and serialisers.
    Required
    Indicates that an action parameter is required.
    Typed
    Used to specify the type of an action parameter.
    UsableAsAction
    Indicates that an action contribution can be used as if it were an action.
    UsableAsFunction
    Indicates that an action can be used as if it were a function.
    ValidInside
    Indicates that an action may only be nested inside a certain other action.

Package com.googlecode.aluminumproject.annotations Description

Various annotations. They are grouped together because some of them (such as @Ignored or Injected) can be applied to classes in more than one package.
